# Testing Workflow

## When Building Features

When implementing or modifying a feature - frontend, backend, or packages - **add tests where possible**. Follow the backend and frontend testing guidelines for conventions.

## Avoid Trivial Tests

Do not write tests that:

- Assert only that a component renders without crashing (with no meaningful assertions)
- Mirror the implementation line-by-line with no added confidence
- Test framework/library behavior rather than project logic
- Cover only auto-generated or purely declarative code (types, config objects, re-exports)

Every test should justify its existence by catching a realistic regression.

## When You Chose Not to Test

If you finish feature work that **could reasonably be tested** but you decided not to, **ask the user** before closing out:

> "I didn't add tests for this change because [reason]. Would you like me to add any?"

**Don't ask** when the change is inherently untestable or trivial - styles, enums, constants, config files, re-exports, type definitions, static assets. Just skip silently.
